content: Easy to use. Love being able to add notes.
Excellent, easy to read, and easy to use meter. I especially like the read-outs for 7, 14, 30 & 90 days. I'm happy to test every morning.
Easy to use and review data
Quick and easy. Graphs your results. No issues.
Easy to use.
Haven't had any problems. Easy to use.
So far so good easy to use
Great app helps me know what my sugar levels are easy to maneuver around the app every diabetic should have this on their phone
Easy to use
Easy of use

Update, still having issues with the app syncing with my meter. My A1c was actually 6.7, but I had to enter it as 7 because there is no way to enter an A1c lab reading with decimals. I would like to be able to be able to enter data more precisely so I can track my trends more accurately. This app is incredibly DIFFICULT to pair, sync, and download information.

I love the concept but it's giving me a headache syncing and how the step goal works because since I got the meter and app it hasn't recorded any steps, and I can't manually adjust it. Hopefully some updates can make it more user friendly.

The app almost never updates with the meter, so much so I just quit trying to update and manually do it. Seems the only good thing about it is that I can show it to my doc without having to take in a notebook !!!

I love the concept but it's giving me a headache syncing and how the step goal works because since I got the meter and app it hasn't recorded any steps, and I can't manually adjust it. Hopefully some updates can make it more user friendly.

App works only when device is not taking a reading therefore you need to turn the meter on by itself. Should be able to sync when you just take a reading or stay on to sync right after you pull the test strip out rather than shutting off immediately. Would nicer if I could sync my meter to my computer without the app sometimes.
Excellent, easy to read, and easy to use meter. I especially like the read-outs for 7, 14, 30 & 90 days. I'm happy to test every morning.

Many times I have to wait for the meter to sync with my phone for minutes. Sometimes the meter will shut off before my reading will register on phone. Then I have to enter it manually. Real pain when I'm in a hurry.
Only thing is it takes many steps to sync with meter.

I appreciate what this app does a little. The logging of the info isn't what's important. Calculating the insulin to take and logging the amount of insulin taken would be a lot more helpful so the glucometer should have that functionality available as well as this app. Though I will admit the tracking and features available in this app are many they just seem to be lacking some very important pieces! Check out the t1d1 app for the functionality I mentioned. Edit: 2 stars because of response tyvm
Love this app as it sinks with my meter and is easy to use.
App has not and will not sync with meter. When will an update to correct this issue be available?

I love the concept but it's giving me a headache syncing and how the step goal works because since I got the meter and app it hasn't recorded any steps, and I can't manually adjust it. Hopefully some updates can make it more user friendly.

Works perfectly and I am now able to track my highs and lows....
Works great!
Good data gathering tool app. The range of options for monitoring trends is adequate. Exporting data to Exel worksheets is well integrated and seamless.
Works great. fool proof.

I like this product, but have a huge problem with the clock management settings. I work overnights and cannot use the setting to accurately time breakfast, lunch, dinner and overnights. How can I fix this, if I can?
It works perfectly
Love this app it works great

This is the best and easiest meter I have every used.It is now 2018 and I still in love with this app. Everything work so well and the it is so easy to use.. It now 2020 and I am still satisfied with my OneTouch Verio Meter. I have not had any problems. I would buy new one, when it's time to update my meter. I would recommend this meter.

Update, still having issues with the app syncing with my meter. My A1c was actually 6.7, but I had to enter it as 7 because there is no way to enter an A1c lab reading with decimals. I would like to be able to be able to enter data more precisely so I can track my trends more accurately. This app is incredibly DIFFICULT to pair, sync, and download information.

The app is pretty cool, and I can sync to my Fitbit account (but only by going through Fitbit to do so), but my biggest issue is that there are only two options when logging sugars: Before Meal and After Meal. Where is Fasting? Bedtime? And a Supplemental option would be nice, too, for those times when you check as a just-in-case. Otherwise, no complaints!

I love the concept but it's giving me a headache syncing and how the step goal works because since I got the meter and app it hasn't recorded any steps, and I can't manually adjust it. Hopefully some updates can make it more user friendly.

App works only when device is not taking a reading therefore you need to turn the meter on by itself. Should be able to sync when you just take a reading or stay on to sync right after you pull the test strip out rather than shutting off immediately. Would nicer if I could sync my meter to my computer without the app sometimes.

The app didn't even see my Verio Flex and cannot pair. The app did not detect the Verio even with Bluetooth on. This is with my Samsung S10+. My Samsung detected the Verio just fine but the Onetouch Reveal app did not see them Verio and therefore couldn't sync.
Makes me more aware of my blood glucose level because it syncs with my testing machine.
